metadata.name: Coronado #161
metadata.description:
This series is about the beauty and charm of imperfection, chaos amidst order, and letting go. It's about knowing that however much control we think we may have, things can all fall apart or burst into something unexpectedly wonderful at any moment, even without our hands tightly on the reigns.

Please see fxtext article linked from main project page for more background on the project and rendering notes.

Some key commands in live mode:

G : Toggle grain
S : Save current resolution
1 : 4000x5000
2 : 6000x7500
3 : 8000x10000
4 : 10000x12500
5 : 12000x15000
6 : 14000x17500
(1-6 work best on Chrome)
(rendering takes longer as resolution increases)

metadata.name: STOP WHALING! #26
metadata.description:
Commercial whaling was banned in 1986. However, Japan, Norway, and Iceland have killed nearly 40,000 large whales since then. 
Over 100,000 dolphins, small whales, and porpoises are also killed in various countries each year.

Please do not support this kind of act!
Support the fight to stop whaling  
https://uk.whales.org/
https://savedolphins.eii.org/
https://www.seashepherdglobal.org/ 


PLEASE CONSIDER WATCHING THOSE TWO VIDEOS

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vAV3annxWLA
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1AE8Mhw-PNA

~EVERY WORK BOUGHT FOR 39tez WILL BE PRINTED ON Hahnemuhle Fine Art PAPER AND SENT TO THE BUYER~
The the whales in this work are illustrated by waves from the sea.
The lines represent the harpoons used to capture and kill...
The various suns, are the last sun that those whales see before dying.
I tried to represent the injuries with colorful colors
This work was made with very simple code on p5js.
There are 17 color palettes.
Every Whale have different dimensions and waves.

metadata.name: Paper City Dreams #6
metadata.description:
A city made of paper,
crafted with care,
using RoughJS and Hashure Gap
to build buildings with flair.

Rectangles stacked on top of each other,
cast shadows on the ground,
a cross-hash adding depth
to the structures all around.

A city of lines and shapes,
a city of texture and hue,
a generative art masterpiece
bringing the paper city to life, anew.

In live mode press "s" to save image (2200 x 3030).

This may take some time to render, please wait.

metadata.name: Foundations #6
metadata.description:
In march of this year, I started working on a new series involving multi-layering, and overriding shapes. Drawing and playing with colors and opacity.
It started with squares and grid, it then involved deformations, and circles and other experimentations.
This path fits with my artistic generative approach: rather than having a completely predefined idea, I start with a simple concept that evolves during creation. Then surprises happened, and I embraced them.

But this year was not like any other: 2022 has gifted me with a new birthday, the one of my son.

Over the past twelve months, I‚Äôve watched him discovering the world surrounding him, learning and trying new things, laughing, or getting frustrated, sad or happy‚Ä¶
While learning to become a parent, I‚Äôve been in an introspection phase where I questioned what it means to be ‚Äúa father‚Äù. What impact will I have on my son, consciously or not?

‚ÄúFoundations‚Äù takes shape in this context: 2 humans trying and exploring while being inspired by each other.
This series is a first of a set of at least 3, that illustrates an idea of what is an ‚ÄúIdentity‚Äù, and what makes us who we are.

The foundations of an identity are laid in the first days of a child‚Äôs life. They will be influenced by many factors; including parenting, cultural environment, life experiences‚Ä¶ 
Of course, as humans we are in constant evolution; life happens, sometimes for the best, sometimes for the worst, and our personality will be impacted‚Ä¶
But this will be a topic for another time. 


Today, we are at the start.
